`‚òÖ Insight ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ`
**The pattern here is reusable:** when a Node.js plugin has native dependencies that may fail to compile, the graceful degradation ladder is: (1) try prebuilt binary variant ‚Üí (2) try compiled variant ‚Üí (3) run in reduced mode. The key mechanism is `optionalDependencies` in package.json (npm won't fail if they don't install) combined with `try { await import() } catch {}` in code (runtime fallback). This same pattern applies to any Node.js project with cross-platform native deps.
